        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 26 at 5:22PM MDT by NWS Salt Lake City UT</headline>
        <description>At 521 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Lake Powell 9 miles southwest of Halls Crossing, moving northeast at
25 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Halls Crossing, Bullfrog, Glen Canyon National Recreation Area, and
Lake Powell.

This storm will be capable of producing strong gusty winds on Lake
Powell. This will lead to a sudden increase in waves and very choppy
waters which will result in hazardous boating conditions. Boaters are
urged to seek safe harbor if possible.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead
to localized flooding. Seek higher ground and do not drive your
vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
